sequenceDiagram
  participant U as User
  participant CS as Content script
  participant SW as Service worker
  participant ID as identity
  participant API as api
  participant K as knowledge / ai
  participant P as Provider composer

  U->>CS: Click Orvex button (explicit per-use action, AD-6 clause 2)
  CS->>SW: Deliver request<br/>providerId, target-account signal if exposed (FR-CF7)
  SW->>SW: Check live Orvex session + active scope (AD-EXT-6)
  alt session absent or expired
    SW-->>U: Fail closed, visible re-auth prompt
  else session valid
    SW->>K: Retrieve + compose enriched bundle<br/>delegated principal (I-4), RYW via api SoR (AD-EXT-7)
    K-->>SW: Enriched bundle
    SW-->>U: Popup shows memory preview, private items flagged
    U->>SW: Per-use consent (FR-CF1)
    SW->>ID: MINT single-target single-use short-TTL token<br/>scope {memory, target, user, composedTextRef}<br/>+ asserted-scope (AD-8, AD-EXT-3/6, Shape 2)
    ID-->>SW: Consented delivery token<br/>(firewall + consent + scope re-resolved & ENFORCED here; breach = refused, not warned)
    SW->>API: Shape 1a compose-validation call<br/>PRESENTING deliveryToken + composedTextRef
    API-->>SW: validated (token RESERVED, hash-equality<br/>check only — audit NOT yet written)
    SW->>CS: Proceed to canary transaction (Shape 1b composeInto port)
    CS->>P: Canary: resolve -> verify-writable -> insert -> read-back (~250ms, AD-EXT-4)
    alt canary success
      P-->>U: Text visible in composer; user reviews, edits, sends (never auto-send, AD-6 clause 4)
      CS->>SW: outcome: injected
    else canary failure
      CS-->>U: Fail loud; branch to copy/paste degrade (§6)
      CS->>SW: outcome: copied (or aborted)
    end
    SW->>API: Shape 1a outcome-report<br/>{deliveryToken, outcome}
    API-->>SW: acknowledged — token SPENT,<br/>authoritative audit recorded (AD-EXT-3/AD-EXT-6)
  end
